Bernanke Wants to See ‘Further Efforts’ to Modify Mortgages

-- B y   S c o t t   L a n m a n
-- 
2011-06-22T19:12:10Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-22/bernanke-wants-to-see-further-efforts-to-modify-mortgages.html
Federal Reserve Chairman  Ben S.
Bernanke  said he’d like to see “further efforts” to modify
terms of mortgages to help the housing market.  Bernanke, speaking today at a press conference in
 Washington , said he would also like to see efforts to “speed
the process of foreclosures and this disposition of foreclosed
homes to clear the market.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Scott Lanman in Washington at 
 slanman@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
